Description: For sale is a Squier Affinity Series Telecaster in Arctic White. Many Fender upgrades have been made to make this thing a real player! The pickups (Neck and bridge) have been replaced with Fender Tex-Mex pickups, the pickguard has been replaced with a Mint colored tele pickguard, Fender neck plate, switchcraft jack, and a Fender Telecaster restoration headstock decal has been applied. The Frets have been leveled and crowned and the setup is spot on. A real player! Please ask all question before bidding. See ALL photos. Paypal only. Lower 48 states only.-Frets have been leveled and crowned, and no sharp fret ends -Neck was lightly rubbed with ultra fine (0000 grade) steel wool to give it more of a satin feel - Fender Restoration Headstock Decal with two coats of clear coat -Fender Tex Mex Pickups (Neck and Bridge) -Fender Neck Plate -Switchcraft jack -Mint colored tele pickguard -Frets have been leveled and crowned, and no sharp fret ends -Neck was lightly rubbed with ultra fine (0000 grade) steel wool to give it more of a satin feel - Fender Restoration Headstock Decal with two coats of clear coat Here are the specs for the guitar:Alder bodyMaple neck with “C”-shaped profile21-fret maple fingerboard25 1/2" scaleMedium jumbo fretsTelecaster pickups with three-way switchingTop-load Telecaster bridgePlease visit the Squier website for more details.***Two things I want to point out. 1) Squier Affinity Telecaster bodies are 1.5 inches thick, while Fender Telecaster bodies are 1.75 inches thick. You probably already know this, but wanted to state it anyway. 2) When I replaced the jack (to a switchcraft), I changed out the plastic jack plate with an old metal one I had laying around. Please see photo. I assure you that the jack is tight and works perfectly, but there were holes left from the previous jack plate. I didn't have time to replace with a better jack plate. It is something you could leave as is or switch out for $5 on your own. PayPal OnlyLower 48 States Only
